text: {{Infobox settlement | official_name = Nduga Regency | native_name = Kabupaten Nduga | native_name_lang = id | image_skyline = | image_alt = | image_caption = | type = Regency | image_seal = Lambang Kabupaten Nduga.png | seal_alt = | motto = | image_map = 91.24.00 Papua Nduga.svg | map_alt = | map_caption = | coordinates = | coordinates_footnotes = | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = | subdivision_type1 = Province | subdivision_name1 = Papua | seat_type = Capital | seat = Kenyam | leader_title = Regent | leader_name = Yairus Gwijangge | leader_title1 = Vice Regent | leader_name1 = Wentius Nimiangge | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = 12941 | elevation_min_m = | elevation_max_m = | elevation_m = | population_as_of = 2019 | population_total = 106354 | population_density_km2 = auto | population_footnotes = | timezone1 = Indonesia Eastern Time | utc_offset1 = +9 | website = | footnotes = | area_code_type = Area code | area_code = (+62) 967 }} Nduga Regency is one of the regencies (kabupaten) in Papua Province of Indonesia. Nduga Regency was separated from Jayawijaya Regency on 4 January 2008. It covers an area of 12,942 km2, and had a population of 79,053 at the 2010 Census.Biro Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2011. The administrative centre is at Kenyam. ==References== Category:Papua (province)
